message.content:
1. Oral supply of certain fatty acids increases their levels in plasma.
2. Oral supply of certain fatty acids increases their levels in cell membranes.
3. The increase in these fatty acids often comes at the expense of omega-6 PUFAs.
4. Omega-6 PUFAs include arachidonic acid (ARA).
5. Omega-6 PUFAs also include linoleic acid.

messages.content:
Statement: Oral supply of these fatty acids increases their levels in plasma and cell membranes, often at the expense of the omega-6 PUFAs arachidonic acid (ARA) and linoleic acid.
